1
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:56,580
Reading people is the Way,

2
00:00:56,680 --> 00:00:58,120
and speaking is the technique.

3
00:00:58,120 --> 00:00:59,800
I will teach you ventriloquism.

4
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:02,120
You can imitate anyone's voice.

5
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:08,680
Grandma.

6
00:01:19,200 --> 00:01:22,039
Who is it? Why are you wailing so early?

7
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:26,260
Please.

8
00:01:29,039 --> 00:01:30,480
Didn't I tell you?

9
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,680
Guyue Studio is closed today.

10
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,560
Master,

11
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,060
we had an appointment.

12
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,200
Her background.

13
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,640
I remember now.

14
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:52,160
Go inside and wait for me.

15
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,490
We've got work. We've got work.

16
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,560
The Yang Gate closes, the Yin Gate opens.

17
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:12,680
Wandering spirits, do not intrude.

18
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:16,200
Let the path to the Underworld be clear.

19
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:22,280
Earthly karma gathers here,

20
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:26,200
and sins of this life are now absolved.

21
00:02:27,079 --> 00:02:28,720
Chen Afeng, oh, Chen Afeng.

22
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,930
Your life was stolen before your time.

23
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,760
Where is your soul on the road to the afterlife?

24
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,440
Xiaomei.

25
00:02:38,280 --> 00:02:39,120
Xiaomei.

26
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:40,440
Afeng.

27
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,440
Is it you? Afeng?

28
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,400
It's so hot.

29
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:45,800
It's so hot.

30
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,040
Xiaomei, there's a fire.

31
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:49,480
The burning hurts so much.

32
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,000
Afeng.

33
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,160
You've suffered so much.

34
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,610
I burn paper money every month.

35
00:02:54,640 --> 00:02:57,280
I just want you to be comfortable over there.

36
00:02:57,600 --> 00:02:58,600
No.

37
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,040
No.

38
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,160
I died so wrongfully!

39
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,320
What is going on?

40
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:08,000
Didn't you die accidentally in the factory fire?

41
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:08,680
Stay back!

42
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:14,360
This spirit has too much resentment.

43
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,620
It's backfiring on me.

44
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,930
Ma'am, please don't come back.

45
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,520
I beg you, just ask one more question for me.

46
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:25,400
I've married into the Zheng family now.

47
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,280
Does he

48
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,240
hate me?

49
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,300
He only hates himself for being blind

50
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,290
and trusting the wrong person.

51
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:36,650
We were not meant to be in this life.

52
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,060
Let's be husband and wife in the next.

53
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:42,880
My Ah Feng.

54
00:03:44,920 --> 00:03:47,040
I haven't spent enough time with you.

55
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:52,680
She said she'd give ten silver dollars.

56
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:55,960
The ghost messenger said...

57
00:03:56,560 --> 00:03:59,220
He was supposed to be reincarnated as an animal.

58
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:03,480
But if someone is willing to be a vegetarian for three years for his sake,

59
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:06,200
and burns this talisman

60
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,840
before his grave,

61
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,780
the ghost messengers won't give him a hard time.

62
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,660
Thank you, Master.

63
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,260
Thank you, Master.

64
00:04:48,159 --> 00:04:49,080
Easy money.

65
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,800
Sir, we're almost there.

66
00:04:53,880 --> 00:04:56,409
Should I stop at the main gate or the side gate?

67
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:01,920
Sir?

68
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:20,440
Help!

69
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,130
Someone's dead!

70
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:23,480
Help!

71
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,560
Jiqing Lane.

72
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:26,640
Lane 18.

73
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,920
You can't even find the way.

74
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,160
How can you work a case?

75
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,290
I can find it myself.

76
00:05:31,360 --> 00:05:33,020
You didn't have to come along.

77
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,060
If not for your uncle, the Inspector,

78
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:38,120
I wouldn't take a policewoman on patrol.

79
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,240
Well then, Captain,

80
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,040
you can head back now.

81
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,980
I'll see this through.

82
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,960
That's the General Temple over there.

83
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,400
Further ahead is Jiqing Lane.

84
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:48,120
Someone, help! Help!

85
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:48,810
Someone!

86
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,010
Officer!

87
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,180
Officer! Officer!

88
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:51,720
Help!

89
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:52,760
Someone died!

90
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,240
I just picked up a passenger.

91
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,370
He was fine at first,

92
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:59,180
but then he started bleeding from his eyes, ears, nose, and mouth.

93
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,040
Come here.

94
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:02,480
Let's go take a look.

95
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:02,800
Okay.

96
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,800
Right over there.

97
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:05,960
I told you to check his identity and info.

98
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:07,360
What kind of research did you do?

99
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,040
Zhang Xiaohu,

100
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,160
you little bastard.

101
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:10,400
You almost got me killed today.

102
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:11,530
How did I offend you?

103
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,800
That woman's husband died by accident.

104
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:14,720
It wasn't a wrongful death.

105
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,920
Your information was wrong.

106
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,040
They said he was smoking in the factory,

107
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,680
accidentally ignited the phosphorus,

108
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:20,680
and burned to death.

109
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,880
But people at the factory said he didn't smoke.

110
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,320
I think there's something fishy.

111
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,760
What does that have to do with you?

112
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:26,890
Are you a detective?

113
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,760
Do they pay you for solving cases?

114
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:30,400
I'm the one paying you.

115
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,220
Okay, okay.

116
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:31,920
I got it.

117
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,600
Goodbye, Master Wu.

118
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:32,880
You...

119
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,440
Thanks.

120
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,920
What bad luck.

121
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,200
Are you sure he's dead?

122
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,080
Yes, I just checked.

123
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,159
He's not breathing.

124
00:06:42,159 --> 00:06:44,960
What exactly happened? Start from the beginning.

125
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,530
Something's wrong.

126
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:55,690
Something's fishy.

127
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:58,409
Let's go.

128
00:07:07,040 --> 00:07:08,560
It's the Evil Spirit Skinning.

129
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:10,360
It's turned into a blood corpse.

130
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:11,040
Come back!

131
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:23,600
Stop!

132
00:07:25,880 --> 00:07:26,600
Don't be rash.

133
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,600
Secure the scene.

134
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:48,480
Where do you think you're going?

135
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,480
Why did you hit me?

136
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:51,460
Police business. Why did you run?

137
00:07:52,840 --> 00:07:54,240
Someone died over there.

138
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,290
If I didn't hide,

139
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:57,159
was I supposed to stay and watch?

140
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,540
How did you know someone died?

141
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:06,180
Criminals usually return to the scene of the crime.

142
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:09,080
Why are you here?

143
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:11,360
I was just passing by.

144
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:12,920
I don't want any trouble.

145
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,600
Let me go!

146
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,010
You're the only witness right now,

147
00:08:17,320 --> 00:08:19,380
so please come to the station with me.

148
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:29,880
Stop running!

149
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:46,480
I...

150
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:47,680
I hit someone.

151
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,460
Where are they?

152
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,920
Where is that person?

153
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,370
That's strange.

154
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:56,960
Where did they go?

155
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:01,000
Hello.

156
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,880
Did I just hit someone?

157
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,300
You didn't hit anyone.

158
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,740
She must have run away.

159
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,520
What about you? Are you hurt?

160
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,640
I'm fine.

161
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,560
Excuse me.

162
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:13,960
Are you on a case?

163
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:17,010
Yao Zhidi, Shencheng Police Department.

164
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:21,680
Hello.

165
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:24,280
Ji Wenxuan, Renjin Chamber of Commerce.

166
00:09:24,280 --> 00:09:25,800
If there are any damages to pay,

167
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,480
or if you need my help with the investigation,

168
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,320
feel free to contact me.

169
00:09:28,320 --> 00:09:28,800
Sure.

170
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:32,740
Did you see which way she went?

171
00:09:33,440 --> 00:09:34,200
Who?

172
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,600
Wait until I get out before you leave.

173
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,530
You were just...

174
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,980
How did you get in here?

175
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:08,320
Your car knocked me in here.

176
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,400
Then... are you hurt?

177
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,880
I'll take you to the hospital.

178
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:23,360
No need.

179
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:26,280
Just drop me off at the intersection ahead.

180
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:27,800
Okay, no problem.

181
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,160
I just heard you say

182
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,840
your name is Ji Wenxuan,

183
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,460
from the Renjin Chamber of Commerce.

184
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:40,400
What's your name?

185
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:44,560
Why would the young master of Shencheng's biggest shipping company

186
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,160
care about

187
00:10:45,200 --> 00:10:46,920
the name of a nobody like me?

188
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,480
It's fine if you don't want to say.

189
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,280
I mean no harm.

190
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,360
Just at that intersection.

191
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:56,360
Stop right there.

192
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,080
I'm sorry.

193
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,280
Here is your compensation.

194
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:17,340
If it's not enough,

195
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,240
or if you need anything else,

196
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,090
contact me anytime.

197
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:42,560
This is enough.

198
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,720
There's no need to keep in touch.

199
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:45,730
I'm leaving.

200
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:50,800
Wu Yue.

201
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:57,520
Juan,

202
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,640
where are you going so late?

203
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,440
Yue.

204
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:03,080
Dali should be home for dinner by now,

205
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:04,860
but there's no sign of him.

206
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:08,960
Oh no.

207
00:12:09,760 --> 00:12:11,600
The rickshaw with the dead body...

208
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,680
was Dali's.

209
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:18,240
Tell me.

210
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:20,000
Where did you get this money?

211
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,480
It... it was on that man.

212
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:23,740
You took money from a dead man.

213
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:25,360
And you deny killing him for it?

214
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:25,840
No.

215
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,850
This is the fare he promised me.

216
00:12:28,040 --> 00:12:29,240
I didn't dare take a penny more.

217
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,000
You pulled the rickshaw for two li,

218
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,560
and he gave you two silver dollars?

219
00:12:32,560 --> 00:12:33,840
Do you take me for a fool?

220
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,840
No, no. It's true.

221
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,000
At the time, I...

222
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,200
Hey, rickshaw! Stop!

223
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,360
Sir, I'm done for the day.

224
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,680
Wait.

225
00:12:40,720 --> 00:12:42,050
You turning down money?

226
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,560
It's very close. Just at the General's Temple.

227
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:44,020
No, sir.

228
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,080
You don't understand.

229
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,600
My wife is pregnant at home.

230
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:47,960
I have to hurry back to take care of her.

231
00:12:47,960 --> 00:12:49,320
Besides, the General's Temple

232
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,580
isn't really on my way.

233
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,220
If you take me back,

234
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:55,240
these two silver dollars are yours.

235
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:55,920
That much?

236
00:13:01,800 --> 00:13:02,330
Alright.

237
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:03,520
Thank you, sir.

238
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:04,320
Please get in.

239
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,200
Let's go.

240
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,760
Furong Street to General's Temple.

241
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,640
Where exactly at Jiangjun Temple?

242
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,960
Near the main entrance.

243
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,720
He didn't say a word on the way.

244
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:18,240
And then?

245
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:21,240
When we got there, he started bleeding from his seven orifices

246
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:21,960
and died.

247
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,040
Then I met you two.

248
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,880
When we met you,

249
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:28,090
he was already dead.

250
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:30,480
From the time you found him dead until you met us,

251
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,680
how much time passed?

252
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:34,840
After I found him dead,

253
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,680
I abandoned the cart and ran.

254
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,060
Until I met you two,

255
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,840
it was less than ten minutes.

256
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:50,090
What do you want?

257
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,000
Sir.

258
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,560
My husband is Man Dali.

259
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,040
He's a rickshaw puller.

260
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,040
I want to ask about his whereabouts.

261
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,100
A rickshaw puller?

262
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,520
The White-Haired Blood Corpse Case.

263
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,320
That's right.

264
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,920
We're holding him at the station.

265
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,880
Sir, can I see him?

266
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:04,920
Please.

267
00:14:05,080 --> 00:14:06,160
This is a serious matter.

268
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:07,080
The station is on lockdown.

269
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,340
You can't just see him.

270
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,920
You're heavily pregnant.

271
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:12,800
Tell you what.

272
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:14,760
Go get 300 silver dollars.

273
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,520
I'll see what I can do.

274
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,440
We don't have that kind of money.

275
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,440
How can you bail him out with no money?

276
00:14:20,440 --> 00:14:21,640
Just wait at the door.

277
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:22,880
Juan, don't worry.

278
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:24,410
I'll figure something out.

279
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:26,760
Officer.

280
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,160
I'm a witness to the case.

281
00:14:29,160 --> 00:14:30,490
Take me to see Yao Zhidi.

282
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:32,650
Captain.

283
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,600
How's the autopsy going?

284
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:36,640
Forensic Doctor Yang is off work.

285
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:37,600
We can't reach her.

286
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:39,000
The body is in the morgue.

287
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,740
That Yang Moli.

288
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,280
Go get her back here for me.

289
00:14:42,280 --> 00:14:42,840
No.

290
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:44,240
I need to investigate the case.

291
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:44,640
Hey,

292
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,480
how can you investigate without an autopsy?

293
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:49,480
Find someone else to run your errands.

294
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,680
I'm not going anyway.

295
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:52,880
Sansheng,

296
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:53,800
you go.

297
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,920
Captain,

298
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,360
forget the autopsy.

299
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,680
Just burn it quickly.

300
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:01,960
What if the White-haired Blood Zombie comes back to life?

301
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,200
Yao Zhidi,

302
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,960
someone is looking for you at the door.

303
00:15:04,960 --> 00:15:05,490
Who is it?

304
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,960
Says she's a witness to the White-haired Blood Zombie case.

305
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:08,600
A woman.

306
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:11,360
Now we can investigate the case.
